    - name: '1-3: The Heavens Open before EzekielThe Glory Storm'
      title: The Heavens Open before EzekielThe Glory Storm
      number: 1-3
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>.</smallcaps>I am Ezekiel  the son of
        Buzi,  a priest. I was living among the Jewish exiles in Babylon  by the
        River Chebar.  One day when I was thirty, <smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps> the heavens opened before my eyes, and I saw visions of God!
        It happened on the fifth day of the fourth month during the fifth year of
        King Jehoiachin\u2019s exile.  It was then that the word of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        was powerfully revealed to me, <smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps> and I felt the mighty hand of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        come upon me! <smallcaps>\u201D is an idiom for the power and presence of
        God overwhelming the prophet.</smallcaps>"
