        of your captivity,  for this is the very day the king of Babylon begins his
        attack on Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: "24:1\u20132"
        content: "    is the ninth panel (I) in the chiastic parallel structure in
          Ezekiel. This section contains an oracle depicting the \u201Ccooking pot\u201D
          judgment on Jerusalem (,  ). This panel I constitutes the corresponding
          parallel with panel I  in ch.  , which contains the oracle describing Ezekiel
          as a \u201Cwatchman\u201D for the house of Israel and in which Jerusalem\u2019s
          fall is invoked and explained.      This sentence is significant, for it
          contains the exact date Nebuchadnezzar would begin to attack Jerusalem.
          No doubt, this prophecy\u2019s fulfillment established Ezekiel\u2019s authority
          as an accurate prophet. See  ;  .    "
