        from east to west. Starting from the north, the tribes are:DanAsherNaphtaliManassehEphraimReubenJudah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSouth of Judah, from the eastern limit to the western limit,
        is the special portion of holy land that you must set aside. The temple complex
        will stand in the center. That land will be 25,000 cubits [[COMMENT(0)]]
        wide and the same length as one of the tribal portions from the east side
        to the west. "
      comments:
      - number: 48:8
        content: '  About 8.29 miles (13.25 kilometers). Also vv.  ,  ,  ,  ,  , 
          .    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The portion that you must set aside for <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        must be 25,000 cubits long and 20,000 cubits [[COMMENT(0)]] wide.
      comments:
      - number: 48:9
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. This is about 6.63 miles (10.6
          kilometers). Compare  . Although the Hebrew is \u201C10,000 cubits\u201D
          (3.31 miles; 5.3 kilometers), this is considered a scribal error by many.
          See v.  .    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHere is how you will divide the sacred section of land. You
        will give the priests a portion of land that is 25,000 cubits in length and
        10,000 cubits [[COMMENT(0)]] in width. The temple of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        will stand inside this area in the center. "
      comments:
      - number: 48:10
        content: '  About 3.31 miles (5.3 kilometers). Also vv.  ,  .    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This will be for the sons of Zadok, the consecrated priests who faithfully
        served me. They did not join with the straying Israelites, as did the other
        Levites who went astray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: It will be a special gift to them from the sacred portion of the land,
        a most holy portion on the border of the Levites.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAlongside the border of the priests, the Levites\u2019 portion
        will be 25,000 cubits in length and 10,000 cubits in width. The whole length
        will be 25,000 cubits and 10,000 cubits in width. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The City of Jerusalem'
      title: The City of Jerusalem
      number: 14
      content: "It is forbidden for them to sell or exchange any part of it. They
        are not to allow anyone else to own this special land, since it is consecrated
        to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThe rest of the special area is 25,000 cubits long and 5,000
        cubits [[COMMENT(0)]] wide. This must be for the common use of the city,
        for houses and pastures. In the middle will be the city of Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: 48:15
        content: '  About 1.66 miles (2.65 kilometers).    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The dimensions of the city will form a square with 4,500 cubits [[COMMENT(0)]]
        on each side. '
      comments:
      - number: 48:16
        content: '  About 1.49 miles (2.39 kilometers). Also vv.  .    '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: There will be an open space of 250 cubits [[COMMENT(0)]] around the
        perimeter of the city.
      comments:
      - number: 48:17
        content: '  About 437.5 feet (132.5 meters).    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThere will remain one strip of land along the sacred portion
        left over that will extend 10,000 cubits to the east of the city and 10,000
        cubits to the west of the city. This portion will be used to grow food for
        the people who work in the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the city workers, drawn from all the tribes of Israel, will farm
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The entire portion of land you must set apart will have a total area
        of 25,000 cubits square, that is, the sacred portion of land for the temple
        together with the area for the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '21-22: Land for the Other Five Tribes'
      title: Land for the Other Five Tribes
      number: 21-22
      content: "\u201CThis 25,000-cubit square will contain the holy portion of the
        priests, the Levites\u2019 land, and the land where the city will be. It
        will be in the middle of the prince\u2019s land, and he will have any land
        remaining on either side of the sacred portion and of the property of the
        city. The prince will have two sections, one stretching from the edge of
        this area to the eastern border of the country, the other stretching from
        the other edge of this area to the western border. These two sections of
        land belonging to the prince will run alongside the borders of the territories
        of Judah and Benjamin. It will lie between those two territories south of
        Judah and north of Benjamin.\u201D"
      comments: []
